> **Circuit DS Version: 0.0.99**

# Circuit Design System — Mandatory Rules

> **⛔ NEVER USE RAW PRIMEVUE COMPONENTS DIRECTLY. ALWAYS USE CIRCUIT DS COMPONENTS.**
>
> Circuit DS provides ALL UI components in two forms. You MUST use Circuit's version — NEVER import an unstyled PrimeVue component on your own:
>
> 1. **Custom components** — Circuit-built wrappers. Import from `@jumpcloud/circuit/components`.
> 2. **Primitives (PT-styled)** — PrimeVue components that Circuit OWNS and styles via passthrough (PT) config. These are imported from `primevue/*` but they ARE Circuit DS components because Circuit's passthrough theme is applied globally. Only the primitives listed in Section 3b are approved — if a PrimeVue component is NOT in that list, DO NOT USE IT.
>
> **If a Circuit custom wrapper exists (Section 3a), NEVER import the PrimeVue equivalent directly.**

Before writing any UI code, you MUST look up the latest tokens and components from the installed Circuit DS package. Never rely on memorized or hardcoded lists — the package evolves.

## 1. Typography — Use Circuit Tokens Only

Never use raw Tailwind text sizes (`text-base`, `text-2xl`), arbitrary values (`text-[14px]`), custom `leading-*`, or inline `font-size` styles.

**How to find available typography tokens:**
- Read the Tailwind preset: `node_modules/@jumpcloud/circuit/dist/tailwind/index.cjs` — look for `fontSize` keys.
- Search for `text-body-` and `text-heading-` patterns in Circuit's dist to discover all current type scale tokens.
- Check existing Circuit component source files in `node_modules/@jumpcloud/circuit/dist/components/` for real usage examples.

```html
<!-- ❌ WRONG -->
<h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold leading-8">Title</h1>

<!-- ✅ CORRECT — use a Circuit heading token -->
<h1 class="text-heading-2">Title</h1>
<p class="text-body-md">Body</p>
```

## 2. Colors — Use Circuit Tokens Only, No Exceptions

Never use hardcoded hex (`text-[#0f202f]`), rgba (`text-[rgba(...)]`), raw Tailwind palette colors (`text-gray-500`, `bg-white`), or inline `color`/`background-color` styles.

**How to find available color tokens:**
- Read the Tailwind preset: `node_modules/@jumpcloud/circuit/dist/tailwind/index.cjs` — look for `colors`, `backgroundColor`, `textColor`, `borderColor` keys to discover all semantic token names.
- Search for `--jc-color-` CSS custom properties in Circuit's dist files to find the full semantic color system.
- Token naming follows the pattern: `{utility}-{component}-{variant}` (e.g. `bg-neutral-surface`, `text-button-primary-base`, `border-field-default`).

```html
<!-- ❌ WRONG -->
<div class="bg-white text-[#0f202f] border-[#e7e9ea]">
<span class="text-gray-500">Subtle</span>

<!-- ✅ CORRECT — use Circuit semantic tokens -->
<div class="bg-neutral-surface text-neutral-base border-neutral-default_solid">
<span class="text-neutral-subtle">Subtle</span>
```

## 3. Components — NEVER USE RAW PRIMEVUE. ALWAYS USE CIRCUIT DS.

> **⛔ THIS IS THE MOST IMPORTANT RULE. NEVER IMPORT A PRIMEVUE COMPONENT DIRECTLY WHEN CIRCUIT DS PROVIDES A CUSTOM WRAPPER FOR IT. ALWAYS USE CIRCUIT'S VERSION.**

Circuit DS provides every UI component you need. There are NO exceptions — if you need a component, it MUST come from Circuit DS (either as a custom component or as an approved PT-styled primitive).

### 3a. Circuit Custom Components (import from `@jumpcloud/circuit/components`)

These wrap or replace PrimeVue primitives with Circuit-specific behavior, styling, and API. **ALWAYS use these instead of their PrimeVue equivalents. Importing the raw PrimeVue version when a Circuit wrapper exists is FORBIDDEN.**

| Circuit Custom Component | Replaces PrimeVue | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| **Panels & Cards** | | |
| `CollapsiblePanel` | `Panel` | Use for all card/panel sections. Supports `toggleable` prop for collapsible behavior. |
| `CardButton` | — | Clickable card with `#leading` and `#trailing` slots. |
| **Messages & Notifications** | | |
| `MessageNotification` | `Message` | Use `title` and `detail` props instead of default slot. Severities: `info`, `success`, `warn`, `error`. |
| `ToastNotification` | `Toast` | Circuit-styled toast messages. Requires `ToastService`; one instance per app. |
| **Forms & Inputs** | | |
| `CheckboxWithLabel` | `Checkbox` | Use when checkbox needs a label (most cases). Has `#label` and `#description` slots. |
| `RadioButtonWithLabel` | `RadioButton` | Use when radio button needs a label. Has `#label` and `#description` slots. |
| `ToggleSwitch` | `ToggleSwitch` | Toggle with optional label/description. |
| `FormField` | — | Form field wrapper with label, tooltip, help text, validation. Always bind `inputId` to input for accessibility. |
| `Password` | `Password` | Password input with toggle mask visibility. |
| `InputOtp` | `InputOtp` | OTP input (4, 6, or 3-3 digit formats). |
| `SelectWithSlots` | `Select` | Use when select needs `#icon` or `#footer` slot content. |
| **Data Table** | | |
| `DataTable` | `DataTable` + `Column` | Takes a `columns` prop array instead of `<Column>` children. Use `markRaw()` for column components. |
| `DataTableToolbar` | — | Toolbar for DataTable with add button, search, filters, saved views, column config, export. |
| `DataTableCellText` | — | Cell renderer for text columns. |
| `DataTableCellLink` | — | Cell renderer for link columns. |
| `DataTableCellToken` | — | Cell renderer for status token columns. |
| `DataTableCellButton` | — | Cell renderer for button columns. |
| `ActionsToolbar` | — | Bulk actions bar for selected table rows. Hides when `selectedItems` is empty. |
| `Paginator` | `Paginator` | Circuit-styled paginator with rows-per-page. |
| **Toolbar Dropdowns** | | |
| `SavedViewsDropdown` | — | Saved views management in DataTableToolbar. |
| `ColumnConfigDropdown` | — | Column configuration in DataTableToolbar. |
| `ExportDropdown` | — | Export functionality in DataTableToolbar. |
| **Menus & Dropdowns** | | |
| `ActionMenu` | — | Props-based menu wrapping PrimeVue Menu. Supports grouping (`group`/`groupOrder`), icons with severity colors (`iconSeverity`), external links, disabled items, auto-truncation. Toggle via ref: `menu.value?.toggle(event)`. |
| `Dropdown` | — | Flexible dropdown with custom trigger slot. |
| **Filters** | | |
| `FilterModal` | — | Filter modal dialog with basic/additional filters. |
| `FilterField` | — | Individual filter field inside FilterModal. |
| `FilterButton` | — | Button to open filters. |
| `FilterChip` | — | Active filter chip (key/operator/value, removable). |
| **Navigation & Layout** | | |
| `AppNavigation` | — | App-level left sidebar navigation with collapsible items. |
| `PageHeader` | — | Page header with title, subtitle, icon, tabs, `#actions` slot, breadcrumbs. |
| `SaveViewPanel` | — | Panel for saving table views. |
| **AI Components** | | |
| `AiAgentButton` | — | AI-themed gradient button for AI assistant. |
| **Dialogs** | | |
| `SeverityDialog` | — | Higher-level dialog for destructive/risky actions. Three severity levels: `sev1`, `sev2`, `sev3`. Includes message banner, markdown body, confirmation input, acknowledgement checkbox. Uses `RichText` internally. |
| **Stepper** | | |
| `Stepper` | `Stepper` | Multi-step workflow indicator. Horizontal/vertical layouts, custom icons, linear mode, built-in Cancel/Previous/Next/Save buttons. Uses `#step-{value}` slots for content. |
| **Rich Text** | | |
| `RichText` | — | Renders markdown-like strings (`**bold**`, `*italic*`, `` `code` ``, `[link](url)`) to safe HTML. Sanitised with DOMPurify. Props: `content`, `tag`, `wrapLines`. |
| **Other** | | |
| `Chip` | `Chip` | Key-value chip with icon, removable. |
| `ProgressSpinner` | `ProgressSpinner` | Spinner with size variants (`small`, `default`, `large`). |
| `LinkText` | — | Styled link text. |
| `TourGuide` | — | Interactive product tour with step-based guidance. |

```ts
// ✅ CORRECT — import from Circuit
import {
  CollapsiblePanel, MessageNotification, CheckboxWithLabel,
  DataTable, DataTableToolbar, DataTableCellText, DataTableCellLink,
  FormField, ActionsToolbar, ToggleSwitch,
  RadioButtonWithLabel, SelectWithSlots, PageHeader, AppNavigation,
  SeverityDialog, Stepper, RichText,
} from '@jumpcloud/circuit/components';

// ✅ CORRECT — types
import type { Action, SelectedItem } from '@jumpcloud/circuit/components';
import type { StepDefinition } from '@jumpcloud/circuit/components';

// ✅ CORRECT — composable
import { useContainer } from '@jumpcloud/circuit/composables';

// ❌ WRONG — never use these directly when Circuit wraps them
import Panel from 'primevue/panel';
import Message from 'primevue/message';
import Checkbox from 'primevue/checkbox';
import DataTable from 'primevue/datatable';
