### 3b. Circuit DS Primitive Components (import from `primevue/*`) — THE ONLY APPROVED PRIMEVUE IMPORTS

> **These are the ONLY PrimeVue components you are allowed to import directly.** They ARE Circuit DS components — Circuit owns and styles them via passthrough (PT) configs. They look and behave like Circuit because Circuit's global PT theme is applied. If a PrimeVue component is NOT in this list, DO NOT USE IT.

**Approved list:**

`Avatar`, `Badge`, `Button`, `Checkbox` (without label only — use `CheckboxWithLabel` when label needed), `Dialog`, `Divider`, `Drawer`, `IconField`, `InputIcon`, `InputGroup`, `InputGroupAddon`, `InputText`, `Menu`, `MultiSelect`, `Popover`, `RadioButton` (without label only — use `RadioButtonWithLabel` when label needed), `RadioButtonGroup`, `Select` (without icon/footer slots — use `SelectWithSlots` when slots needed), `SelectButton`, `Skeleton`, `Stepper`/`StepList`/`Step`/`StepPanels`/`StepPanel`/`StepItem`, `Tabs`/`TabList`/`Tab`/`TabPanels`/`TabPanel`, `Tag`, `Textarea`, `TieredMenu`, `Tooltip` (directive)

```ts
// ✅ CORRECT — these are Circuit DS primitives, styled by Circuit's passthrough config
import Button from 'primevue/button';
import Tag from 'primevue/tag';
import SelectButton from 'primevue/selectbutton';
import Dialog from 'primevue/dialog';

// ❌ WRONG — these PrimeVue components have Circuit custom wrappers, NEVER import directly
import Panel from 'primevue/panel';        // → use CollapsiblePanel from @jumpcloud/circuit/components
import Message from 'primevue/message';    // → use MessageNotification from @jumpcloud/circuit/components
import Checkbox from 'primevue/checkbox';  // → use CheckboxWithLabel from @jumpcloud/circuit/components
import DataTable from 'primevue/datatable'; // → use DataTable from @jumpcloud/circuit/components

// ❌ WRONG — this PrimeVue component is NOT in the approved primitives list
import Accordion from 'primevue/accordion'; // NOT a Circuit DS component, do not use
```

**How to verify:** Check `node_modules/@jumpcloud/circuit/dist/src/primevue-primitives/` for the full list of Circuit DS primitive components. If a `.js` file exists there, the component is part of Circuit DS. If it does NOT exist there AND there is no Circuit custom wrapper, DO NOT USE IT — ask the user first.

