### 3d. Key Component Usage Patterns

These patterns come from the official Circuit DS docs. Follow them exactly.

| Component | Pattern / Gotcha |
|---|---|
| `Button` | Use `#icon` slot with `iconProps.class` for leading icons. `loading` prop disables and replaces content with spinner. |
| `FormField` | Always bind `inputId` from the default slot to the input's `:id` for accessibility: `<template #default="{ inputId }">`. |
| `DataTable` | Always use `markRaw()` for column components. Use `#toolbar` slot for `DataTableToolbar`, `#empty` and `#initialEmpty` for empty states. See Section 6 for the full mandatory list page pattern. When a `DataTableCellLink` column `onClick` and `@row-click` both call the same idempotent handler, this is **intended behavior — NOT a bug**. Both the row and the cell link should be clickable; do not add `e.stopPropagation()`. |
| `DataTableToolbar` | **Always** inside `DataTable`'s `#toolbar` slot — never as a sibling. Primary "Add" button via `add-button-label` prop. See Section 6. |
| `ActionsToolbar` | **Always** absolutely positioned floating over the table bottom (`absolute bottom-16 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 z-10`), wrapped in `<Transition>`. See Section 6. |
| `Checkbox` (primitive) | Only use raw `Checkbox` from `primevue/checkbox` when NO label is needed. For labeled checkboxes, ALWAYS use `CheckboxWithLabel`. |
| `RadioButton` (primitive) | Only use raw `RadioButton` from `primevue/radiobutton` when NO label is needed. For labeled radios, ALWAYS use `RadioButtonWithLabel`. |
| `RadioButtonGroup` | Horizontal by default. Use `class="flex-col"` for vertical layout. |
| `Select` (primitive) | Only use raw `Select` from `primevue/select` when NO icon or footer slots are needed. For slots, use `SelectWithSlots`. |
| `Dialog` | Always use `#closeicon` with `<XMarkIcon />`, `:draggable="false"`, `modal`. See Section 7. |
| `Drawer` | Use `#closebutton` slot with `btnProps.closeCallback`. Sizes: `sm` (288px), `md` (384px), `lg` (480px), `xl` (640px). |
| `Tabs` | Custom `withPadding` prop adds 24px horizontal padding. Tab descriptions use `text-body-md text-tab-sub-text-base`. |
| `Tooltip` | This is a **directive**, not a component: `v-tooltip.top="'Text'"`. |
| `ToastNotification` | Requires `ToastService` plugin. Only one `<ToastNotification />` instance per app. |
| `SelectButton` | Bar variant: wrap in `div` with `px-6 py-3 border-b border-neutral-default_solid`. |
| `AppNavigation` | `topnav-action-buttons` slot only renders on mobile/tablet. |
| `SeverityDialog` | Three severity levels: `sev1` (standard), `sev2` (critical with message banner), `sev3` (requires confirmation input and/or acknowledgement checkbox). Use `dialogContent` for markdown body text, `messageContent` for plain-text banner. Use `actionHandler` with `close()` callback for async/loading actions. |
| `Stepper` | Use `v-model:value` with string step values. Steps defined via `steps` prop (array of `StepDefinition`). Content via `#step-{value}` slots. Use `linear` for sequential-only navigation. Use `nextDisabled` to block Next/Save. Custom buttons via `#buttons` slot. |
| `RichText` | Default `tag` is `span`. Use `tag="div"` with `:wrapLines="true"` for multi-paragraph content. Only supports `**bold**`, `*italic*`, `` `code` ``, `[link](url)`. Content is sanitised with DOMPurify. |
| `ActionMenu` | Toggle via template ref: `menu.value?.toggle(event)`. Use `group` + `groupOrder` for sectioned menus. Use `iconSeverity: 'danger'` for destructive items. Use `menuClass="w-[180px]"` for width control. |
| `useContainer` | Composable from `@jumpcloud/circuit/composables`. Returns `containerElement` ref. Use to bind `appendTo` on overlays (Dialog, Popover, Menu) in MFE environments. |

### 3e. Component Not Found?

**If a needed component does not exist in Circuit DS (neither custom nor PT-styled), ASK the user** whether to create a new reusable component or use a one-off solution. Never silently build a duplicate.

## 4. Figma Code Connect — Finding the Right Component

When implementing from a Figma design, use the Figma MCP server's Code Connect features before writing any code:

1. **`get_code_connect_map`** — Pass the Figma node ID to get mapped component source paths and names.
2. **`get_code_connect_suggestions`** — Get suggestions for linking a Figma node to code components.
3. **`get_design_context`** — Get full design context including component structure and styling.

Always check Code Connect first to find the correct Circuit component and its import path. Use the mapped component exactly as specified.

## 5. Spacing & Border Radius

Never use arbitrary spacing (`p-[12px]`) or radius (`rounded-[8px]`) values.

**How to find available tokens:**
- Read the Tailwind preset for `spacing` and `borderRadius` keys to discover all Circuit aliases (e.g. `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`).

## 6. List Page Pattern — DataTable + DataTableToolbar (Mandatory)

> **⛔ Every list/table page MUST follow this exact pattern. No exceptions.**

On list pages, `DataTableToolbar` goes inside `DataTable`'s `#toolbar` slot. `ActionsToolbar` floats over the table using absolute positioning. `FilterModal` is a sibling at the same level.

### 6a. Complete Reference Example

This is the **canonical pattern** for every list page. Follow it exactly:

```html
<div class="flex flex-col h-full relative">
  <DataTable
    :data="currentPageData"
    :columns="columns"
    :loading="loading"
    selection-mode="multiple"
    v-model:selection="selection"
    :paginator="true"
    :rows="rows"
    :first="first"
    :total-records="totalRecords"
    :lazy="true"
    scrollable
    scroll-height="flex"
    @update:first="(v) => first = v"
    @update:rows="(v) => rows = v"
    @page-change="handlePageChange"
    @row-click="handleRowClick"
  >
    <template #toolbar>
      <DataTableToolbar
        ref="toolbarRef"
        :loading="loading"
        add-button-label="Add Item"
        search-placeholder="Search items..."
        :saved-views="savedViews"
        :default-views="defaultViews"
        :selected-view-id="selectedViewId"
        :columns="columnConfigs"
        :export-options="exportOptions"
        :active-filters="activeFiltersData"
        :show-save-view-button="true"
        :show-save-view-panel="showSaveViewPanel"
        :sort-options="sortOptions"
        :visible-columns-count="visibleColumnsCount"
        @add="handleAdd"
        @search="handleSearch"
        @filter="handleFilter"
        @refresh="handleRefresh"
        @view-select="handleViewSelect"
        @column-visibility-change="handleColumnVisibilityChange"
        @export-select="handleExportSelect"
        @filter-remove="handleFilterRemove"
        @clear-all="handleClearAll"
        @save-view="handleSaveView"
        @save-view-submit="handleSaveViewSubmit"
        @save-view-cancel="handleSaveViewCancel"
      />
    </template>

    <template #empty>
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-16 text-neutral-subtle">
        <span class="text-body-md">No items match your filters</span>
        <span class="text-body-sm mt-1">Try adjusting your search or filter criteria</span>
      </div>
    </template>

    <template #initialEmpty>
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center py-16 text-neutral-subtle">
        <span class="text-body-md">No items yet</span>
        <span class="text-body-sm mt-1">Add your first item to get started</span>
      </div>
    </template>
  </DataTable>

  <!-- ActionsToolbar — Floating over the table when items selected -->
  <Transition
    enter-active-class="transition-all duration-200 ease-out"
    enter-from-class="opacity-0 translate-y-4"
    enter-to-class="opacity-100 translate-y-0"
    leave-active-class="transition-all duration-150 ease-in"
    leave-from-class="opacity-100 translate-y-0"
    leave-to-class="opacity-0 translate-y-4"
  >
    <div
      v-if="selectedItems.length > 0"
      class="absolute bottom-16 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 z-10"
    >
      <ActionsToolbar
        :actions="bulkActions"
        :selected-items="selectedItems"
        :selection-label="selection.length === 1 ? 'Item selected' : 'Items selected'"
        @action="handleBulkAction"
        @close="handleClearSelection"
      />
    </div>
  </Transition>

  <!-- FilterModal -->
  <FilterModal
    v-model:visible="showFilterModal"
    :basic-filters="basicFilters"
    :additional-filters="additionalFilters"
    :applied-filters="appliedFilters"
    @apply="handleFilterApply"
    @clear-all="handleFilterClearAll"
  />
</div>
```

### 6b. Key Rules

| Rule | Detail |
|---|---|
| `DataTableToolbar` location | **Always** inside `DataTable`'s `#toolbar` slot — never as a sibling element |
| `ActionsToolbar` location | **Always** absolutely positioned floating over the table bottom, wrapped in `<Transition>` |
| `FilterModal` location | Sibling of `DataTable`, inside the same `relative` container |
| Container | Outer `div` must have `class="flex flex-col h-full relative"` |
| Scrolling | `DataTable` must have `scrollable` and `scroll-height="flex"` for flex-based scrolling |
| Pagination | Use `DataTable`'s built-in `:paginator="true"` with `:rows`, `:first`, `:total-records`, `:lazy` |
| Empty states | Use `#empty` slot (filtered, no results) and `#initialEmpty` slot (no data at all) |

### 6c. Primary Add Button Rule

On **list/table pages**, the primary "Add" action (e.g. "Add Asset", "Add Application", "Add User") **MUST** use the `DataTableToolbar`'s built-in add button via the `add-button-label` prop. Never place a separate primary add button in the `PageHeader` actions when a `DataTableToolbar` is present on the page.

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `showAddButton` | `boolean` | `true` | Show/hide the built-in primary add button |
| `addButtonLabel` | `string` | `"Add"` | Label text — customize per context (e.g. `"Add Asset"`, `"Add User"`) |

```html
<!-- ❌ WRONG — separate add button in PageHeader when toolbar exists -->
<PageHeader title="Devices">
  <template #actions>
    <Button label="Add Device" />   <!-- Don't do this -->
  </template>
</PageHeader>
```

### 6d. What Goes in PageHeader Actions?

`PageHeader` `#actions` slot is for **secondary/contextual actions** that apply to the whole page, not to the table. Examples:
- Settings button (navigates to settings)
- Export/Import at a page level
- Actions dropdown on detail views

### 6e. Common Mistakes

| Mistake | Correct Approach |
|---|---|
| Placing `DataTableToolbar` as a sibling above `DataTable` | Put it inside `DataTable`'s `#toolbar` slot |
| Building a custom toolbar with `InputText` + icons | Use `DataTableToolbar` inside `#toolbar` slot |
| Placing `ActionsToolbar` inline in the layout flow | Use absolute positioning with `bottom-16 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 z-10` |
| Missing `<Transition>` on `ActionsToolbar` | Always wrap in `<Transition>` with enter/leave animation classes |
| Forgetting `relative` on the container div | Required for `ActionsToolbar` absolute positioning |
| Using custom pagination below the table | Use `DataTable`'s built-in `:paginator="true"` prop |
| Using custom empty state divs outside the table | Use `#empty` and `#initialEmpty` slots inside `DataTable` |

## 7. Dialog — Circuit DS Primitive Usage

`Dialog` is a **Circuit DS primitive component** — it is PrimeVue's `Dialog` styled by Circuit's passthrough (PT) configuration. Always import from `primevue/dialog`. Circuit's PT provides styled header (`text-heading-3`), content padding (`p-md`), footer layout (`flex gap-md`), close button, overlay backdrop, and transitions automatically.

```ts
// ✅ CORRECT — Circuit DS primitive
import Dialog from 'primevue/dialog';
```

### Required Props

Always set these props on every Dialog:

| Prop | Value | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `v-model:visible` | `ref<boolean>` | Controls open/close state |
| `modal` | — | Shows backdrop overlay |
| `:draggable="false"` | `false` | Dialogs should not be draggable |
| `header` | `string` | Dialog title text (or use `#header` slot) |

### Reference Example — This Is the Correct Pattern

```html
<Dialog
  v-model:visible="showDialog"
  :draggable="false"
  modal
  header="Dialog Header"
  :style="style"
  :showHeader="showHeader"
>
  <template #closeicon><XMarkIcon /></template>

  <!-- Default slot: content -->
  <p>Dialog body content goes here.</p>

  <!-- Footer slot: left content + right buttons -->
  <template #footer>
    <div class="flex items-center w-full">Footer left content</div>
    <div class="flex gap-sm">
      <Button label="Cancel" severity="secondary" variant="text" @click="showDialog = false" />
      <Button label="Save" />
    </div>
  </template>
</Dialog>
```

### Key Slots

| Slot | Purpose | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| default | Dialog body content | Auto-styled with `p-md`, borders, `gap-md` |
| `#header` | Custom header content | Use when you need icons or complex header layout |
| `#closeicon` | Custom close icon | Use `<XMarkIcon />` from `@heroicons/vue/24/outline` |
| `#footer` | Footer with actions | Circuit PT styles as `flex gap-md` — place two sibling divs (see below) |

### Footer Structure

Circuit's PT styles the `#footer` slot as `flex gap-md`. Use **two sibling divs** inside:

1. **Left div** — `class="flex items-center w-full"` — for left-aligned content (optional text, links, info)
2. **Right div** — `class="flex gap-sm"` — for action buttons (Cancel + Save)

```html
<template #footer>
  <div class="flex items-center w-full">Optional left content</div>
  <div class="flex gap-sm">
    <Button label="Cancel" severity="secondary" variant="text" @click="showDialog = false" />
    <Button label="Save" />
  </div>
</template>
```

If you only need right-aligned buttons (no left content), you can use a single div:

```html
<template #footer>
  <div class="flex items-center w-full"></div>
  <div class="flex gap-sm">
    <Button label="Cancel" severity="secondary" variant="text" @click="showDialog = false" />
    <Button label="Confirm" />
  </div>
</template>
```

### Optional Props

| Prop | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `:showHeader` | `boolean` | Show/hide the header section |
| `:closable` | `boolean` | Show/hide the close button (default `true`) |
| `:style` | `object` | Set dialog width — e.g. `:style="{ width: '560px' }"` |

### Sizing

Use `:style="{ width: 'Npx' }"` for dialog width. Common sizes:
- Small dialogs (simple forms): `480px`
- Medium dialogs (multi-field forms): `560px`
- Large dialogs (complex content, tables): `600px`–`720px`

### Fullscreen Dialogs

For fullscreen dialogs, use the `maximizable` prop with the `fullscreenInnerWidth` attribute:

```html
<Dialog :maximizable="true" fullscreenInnerWidth="1024px">
```

### Common Mistakes

| Mistake | Correct Approach |
|---|---|
| Building a custom modal with `div` + backdrop | Use `Dialog` from `primevue/dialog` |
| Using `Drawer` when a centered modal is needed | Use `Dialog` — Drawer is for side panels |
| Forgetting `modal` prop | Always set `modal` for backdrop overlay |
| Forgetting `:draggable="false"` | Always disable dragging |
| Wrapping footer buttons in a single `justify-end` div | Use two sibling divs: left content (`w-full`) + right buttons (`gap-sm`) |
| Putting action buttons in the default slot | Use the `#footer` slot for action buttons |
| Using `@hide` to close | Use `v-model:visible` with a `ref` |
| Not using `#closeicon` slot | Use `<XMarkIcon />` for the close icon |

## 8. SeverityDialog — Destructive Action Dialogs

`SeverityDialog` is a **Circuit custom component** for risky or destructive actions. It wraps `Dialog` and adds severity-specific styling, message banners, markdown content, and confirmation safeguards. **Always use `SeverityDialog` instead of building custom destructive confirmation dialogs.**

```ts
import { SeverityDialog } from '@jumpcloud/circuit/components';
```

### Severity Levels

| Level | Use Case | Safeguards |
|---|---|---|
| `sev1` | Standard confirmations | Action + Cancel buttons only |
| `sev2` | Critical actions with impact warnings | Message banner + Action + Cancel |
| `sev3` | Irreversible destructive actions | Message banner + confirmation input and/or acknowledgement checkbox |

### Basic Usage (sev1)

```html
<SeverityDialog
  v-model:visible="visible"
  dialogTitle="Confirm Action"
  variant="sev1"
  messageTitle="Warning"
  dialogContent="This will **permanently** remove the resource."
  actionText="Delete"
  cancelText="Cancel"
  @action="handleAction"
  @cancel="visible = false"
/>
```

### With Confirmation Input (sev3)

```html
<SeverityDialog
  v-model:visible="visible"
  dialogTitle="Delete Resource"
  variant="sev3"
  messageTitle="Irreversible Action"
  messageContent="This cannot be undone."
  :showMessageIcon="true"
  dialogContent="This will **permanently** delete all associated data."
  :confirmationValue="'DELETE'"
  confirmationText="To proceed, enter <value>."
  acknowledgementText="I understand this action is _irreversible_."
  actionText="Delete"
  cancelText="Cancel"
  @action="handleDelete"
  @cancel="visible = false"
/>
```

### With Loading State (sev2 + actionHandler)

```html
<SeverityDialog
  v-model:visible="visible"
  dialogTitle="Critical Action"
  variant="sev2"
  messageTitle="Impact Warning"
  messageContent="Service impact may extend to other systems."
  :showMessageIcon="true"
  :isLoading="isLoading"
  :actionHandler="handleAction"
  dialogContent="Please review the **service impact** before continuing."
  actionText="Proceed"
  cancelText="Cancel"
  @cancel="visible = false"
/>
```

Use `actionHandler` when you need async behavior. It receives a `close()` callback; return `false` to keep the dialog open and call `close()` manually after async work completes.

## 9. Stepper — Multi-Step Workflows

`Stepper` is a **Circuit custom component** that wraps PrimeVue's Stepper primitive with built-in navigation buttons, state management, and Circuit styling.

```ts
import { Stepper } from '@jumpcloud/circuit/components';
import type { StepDefinition } from '@jumpcloud/circuit/components';
```

### Basic Usage

```vue
<template>
  <Stepper
    :steps="steps"
    v-model:value="activeStep"
    @cancel="handleCancel"
    @save="handleSave"
  >
    <template #step-1>
      <div class="text-body-md text-neutral-base">Step 1 content</div>
    </template>
    <template #step-2>
      <div class="text-body-md text-neutral-base">Step 2 content</div>
    </template>
    <template #step-3>
      <div class="text-body-md text-neutral-base">Step 3 content</div>
    </template>
  </Stepper>
</template>

<script setup>
import { ref } from 'vue';
import { Stepper } from '@jumpcloud/circuit/components';

const activeStep = ref('1');
const steps = [
  { value: '1', label: 'Account Setup' },
  { value: '2', label: 'Profile Details' },
  { value: '3', label: 'Confirmation' },
];
</script>
```

### Key Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `steps` | `StepDefinition[]` | — | Array of step definitions (required) |
| `value` | `string \| number` | — | Active step (v-model:value) |
| `vertical` | `boolean` | `false` | Vertical layout |
| `linear` | `boolean` | `false` | Sequential-only navigation |
| `showCancelButton` | `boolean` | `true` | Show Cancel button |
| `nextDisabled` | `boolean` | `false` | Disable Next/Save button |
| `outlineButtons` | `boolean` | `false` | Outline variant for nav buttons |
| `saveLabel` | `string` | `'Save'` | Last step button label |

### With Custom Icons

```ts
import { CloudArrowUpIcon, CogIcon, ShieldCheckIcon } from '@heroicons/vue/24/outline';

const steps = [
  { value: '1', label: 'Upload', icon: CloudArrowUpIcon },
  { value: '2', label: 'Configure', icon: CogIcon },
  { value: '3', label: 'Deploy', icon: ShieldCheckIcon },
];
```

### Built-in Button Behavior

| Step Position | Buttons Shown |
|---|---|
| First step | Cancel + Next |
| Middle steps | Cancel + Previous + Next |
| Last step | Cancel + Previous + Save |

## 10. Composables

Circuit DS exports composables from `@jumpcloud/circuit/composables`.

| Composable | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `useContainer` | Returns `containerElement` ref for MFE-aware overlay mounting. Bind to `appendTo` on Dialog, Popover, Menu, etc. in micro-frontend environments. |

```ts
import { useContainer } from '@jumpcloud/circuit/composables';

const { containerElement } = useContainer();
```

```html
<Dialog :appendTo="containerElement" ... />
```

## 11. Pre-Implementation Checklist

Before writing any UI code, always:
1. Look up current Circuit typography tokens from the Tailwind preset.
2. Look up current Circuit color tokens from the Tailwind preset.
3. Check `@jumpcloud/circuit/components` exports FIRST for a custom component match.
4. If no custom component exists, check `primevue-primitives/` for a PT-styled primitive.
5. If implementing from Figma, check Code Connect first via the MCP server.
6. If no matching component exists in Circuit DS at all, ask the user before creating a new one.
7. For destructive actions, use `SeverityDialog` — never build custom confirmation dialogs.
8. For multi-step workflows, use `Stepper` — never build custom step indicators.
